The following is an archived discussion of the DYK nomination of the article below. Please do not modify this page. Subsequent comments should be made on the appropriate discussion page (such as this nomination's talk page, the article's talk page or Wikipedia talk:Did you know), unless there is consensus to re-open the discussion at this page. No further edits should be made to this page.

The result was: promoted by Keilana (talk) 04:44, 2 September 2015 (UTC)

Adam Stansfield

[edit]

... that footballer Adam Stansfield, who died in 2010, is featured on legal tender banknotes in the English city of Exeter?

Reviewed: Jake Olson (gridiron football)

Improved to Good Article status by The Almightey Drill (talk) and Mattythewhite (talk). Nominated by The Almightey Drill (talk) at 18:34, 18 August 2015 (UTC).

: Article has been expanded and improved to good article status. 116 characters total (including punctuation). Article appears to be within policy, sources, etc. User:The Almightey Drill's QAQ was promoted.

One change I would make would be "...is featured on legal tender..." instead of "...features on legal tender..." - Neutralhomer • Talk • 00:23, 29 August 2015 (UTC)
